<subSubSection id="B016B387FBAD7119493B0781833EAC85" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="FC1AC7580BCC8639F82B30BAC4005F53" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="755C896AA9FAB3AC00465A4A42A39715" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A slender trailing or twining herb, stems glabrous. Leaves petiolate, 1-5.5 
<normalizedToken id="BB7DCD991CE7E50313435CDE0F3C8E8E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-6 cm, ovate, acuminate, mucronulate, base hastate, auricles rounded or angled, margin dentate with large teeth, strigose on both surfaces or glabrous adaxially; petioles 0.5-4 cm. Inflorescence of solitary or paired flowers from the leaf axils; peduncles 1.2-4.8 cm, erect; bracteoles 1-2 mm, lanceolate; pedicels 4-13 mm, thicker than peduncles, becoming reflexed; sepals unequal, glabrous, strongly muricate, outer 3-4 
<normalizedToken id="A78940BCEF02E3B28CFDB839AE653D95" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, ovate, acute or obtuse, often mucronate, inner 5-8 
<normalizedToken id="99974BDF8AAA6C431F1AE9A478D57298" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, oblong-lanceolate, mucronate; corolla 4-5.5 cm long, funnel-shaped, pink or purplish, glabrous, limb 4-5 cm diam. Capsules 8 
<normalizedToken id="7BA3E388285B19E8BBD0E556C690EC2E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6 mm, conical, glabrous; seeds 5 
<normalizedToken id="176DBBA03242E32D3B1A2A6F52D2EDD5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 mm, puberulent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
